rComments: Prof. Hjartarson works for the Ontario government and as a consequence his lectures tend to focus on whatever is currently occupying his time during his day job. His assignments are applied rather than academic which I found to be annoying. He would be much better suited to teaching at Ryerson where his particular brand of teaching is more common.

Although Professor Hjartarson obviously knew if stuff, I found his bias toward the Ontario Liberal provincial government (he works for the McGuinty;s government while teaching)to be reflected in almost all aspects of lecture. Despite this, Hjartarson is very approachable, and has a kind of nerdy quality which is quite endearing.
